1. What is Flow Designer?

Flow Designer is a no-code/low-code automation tool in ServiceNow used to:

Automate business processes

Trigger actions based on events

Connect multiple applications

Replace legacy workflows

It uses:

Triggers â†’ start the flow

Actions â†’ perform tasks

Data Pills â†’ pass data between steps

2. Key Components of a Flow
ðŸ”¹ Trigger

Defines when the flow starts
Examples:

Record created

Record updated

Scheduled time

Service Catalog submission

ðŸ”¹ Actions

Tasks performed after trigger
Examples:

Create Record

Send Email

Update Record

Create Task

Wait for condition

ðŸ”¹ Data Pills

Reusable data objects passed between steps
Used to:

Fill form fields

Set conditions

Share values between actions

3. Steps to Create a Flow

Open Flow Designer

Click New â†’ Flow

Enter:

Flow Name

Description

Application scope

Add a Trigger

Add one or more Actions

Use Data Pills where required

Click Save

Click Activate

4. Example Flow (Basic Use Case)

Use Case:
When a new Incident is created â†’ Send an Email to the assigned user

Steps:

Trigger â†’ Record Created (Incident table)

Action â†’ Send Email

Email recipient â†’ Assigned to (Data Pill)

Email body â†’ Incident details

Save and Activate

5. Testing a Flow

Create or update a record based on the trigger

Check:

Email delivery

Record updates

Task creation

Use Execution Details for debugging

